@node WHATIS "LinkUP: What is it?"
LinkUP is a program to connect a Z88 to an Amiga to transfer files between the
two.

It started life when I downloaded several other link programs from Aminet and
found that only one of the three worked on my system and this had no GUI -
FileZ88. So I wrote some software myself !
@endnode


@node NEED

                What you need to run LinkUP


A copy of the Program - You have if you are reading this !
An Amiga to Z88 cable - See below

@{b}Z88 9 Pin         Amiga 25 Pin@{ub}
2 ------------------------- 3
3 ------------------------- 2
4 ------------------------- 5
5 ------------------------- 4
7 ------------------------- 7
8 ------------------------- 20
9 ------------------------- 6+8


Connect the pins as above.
Note, I havent been able to get a cable hood to go over the 9 pin connector as
it stops the D plug going all the way into the Z88.


If you happen to have a PC link cable then use this as it is the same cable.




@{b}The Software@{ub}

Updates are available from either the Aminet or my Web page at
@{b}http://homepagers.tripod.com/matkey/@{ub}

I will also put all the other Amiga to Z88 programs onto this page.




@endnode

