@node USAGE "LinkUP: Usage."

On the Z88 set the baud rate to 1200 for both send and receive and then 
start up "Import Export" by pressing []X.


The buttons on the Amiga program are self explanatory, however if you 
come from Mars or something they are explained below 
-Select-  selects the file you want to send to the Z88 
-Send-    downloads the file to the Z88
-Receive- upload the file from the Z88 to the Amiga

@{b}To send a file to the Z88@{ub}
Put the Z88 in receive mode by pressing "R" in Import/Export
Select the file you want via the file requestor and click on send


@{b}At the moment you have to load the text in Pipedream by selecting
"Load as Plain Text" on the file load menu.
Sorry! - its a sod to get around but I am working on it !
@{ub}




@{b}To receivce a File from the Z88@{ub}
Click on Receive on the Amiga
Press "T" , return, and then the file you want to send on the Z88


@endnode


